description:
&lt;p&gt;We are currently looking forward to recruit a dynamic Band 5 Registered Nurse with at least more than significant experience for our busy but friendly Haematology Day Unit. We look after patients with different haematology conditions on our department which has 11 chairs. It is a fast paced department where you develop excellent time management skills while extending your nursing skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our Registered Nurses take great pride in providing quality and compassionate patient care. These roles are essential to the experience of our patients and their relatives and carers and they complement the clinical care provided by our multi-disciplinary team of doctors and therapists. In addition the Band 5 assists in quality initiatives, supports more junior staff and takes a leading role within the department.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Mercy Mutsondi&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Haematology Day Unit/Outpatient&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Manager Email address: mercy.mutsondi@uhcw.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 02476965490&lt;/p&gt;
